HEADWORD: Self-devotion
<hw>Self`-de*vo"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
devoting one's self, or the state of being self-devoted; willingness to
sacrifice one's own advantage or happiness for the sake of others;
self-sacrifice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Self-devouring</ent>⟦br⟧
